                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red; blue.</seg>
                        <date>First half of 19th cent.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donors; incipits of the
                           sections and chapters; numbers of the chapters; the word mǝʿrāf; elements
                           of the punctuation signs, Ethiopic numerals; element of the quires marks;
                           ruling lines in the Canon tables. 
 On the incipit page of each
                           Gospel, a few lines are rubricated (two red line alternating with black
                           ones).  Streched rubricated script is used for some passages in the
                           Introduction and the Biblical text, s. <locus target="#141ra">141ra</locus>,
                           142vb-143ra, etc.</seg>
                        <note>- The scribe highlighted some chapters using line break after the chapter
                           number, before its incipit (s. e.g., <locus target="#18va">18va</locus>,
                           21r)</note>
                        
                        <note>- For the Introductions, Biographies of the Evangelists etc., smaller
                           script is used.</note>
                        
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Rubricated passages were probably
                        executed by a different
                        scribe.
                       
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">- <locus from="9ra" to="11ra">9ra-11ra</locus>: Simple, elegant, coloured (red) vertical ornamental
                        bands (geometric motifs) are incerted in the middle of each page, separating
                        the groups of the Canon Tables.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote xml:id="d2">Additional leaves with miniatures were infixed in the recent time, to
                        "illuminate" the Ms.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
